newsitem.title: USA: KCBT wheat ends lower after late liquidation.
newsitem.headline: KCBT wheat ends lower after late liquidation.

text.p: KCBT hard red winter wheat futures drifted for most of the session on a lack of news, but ended lower after a late bout of commission-type liquidation, traders said.

"FIMAT turned seller late in the day. They sold about 6-1/2 million bushels in the last 30 minutes of the session," a trader said. "Dreyfus held it up, along with the locals, who were definitely buying the back months."
There was little news to move Friday's market, and traders said volumes were substantially lighter than those seen during Thursday's sell-off.

KCBT wheat settled 3-1/2 cents per bushel lower to one cent higher, with December down 3-1/2 cents at $4.01. New contract lows were set in all months out to May 1997, with Dec setting a new low at $3.98.
Traders said the Dec/March spread narrowed to 18 cents late, after having traded at 21 cents earlier.

FIMAT sold 2.1 million Dec, 2.6 million March, 1.7 million May and 1.4 million July. CIS bought 2.5 million Dec bushels. Term Commodities bought two million July. General Mills bull-spread 1.6 million Dec/March bushels at 19 to 21 cents.
